      • insertAndGetID

        protected java.lang.String insertAndGetID(java.lang.String[] columnNames,
                                          java.lang.Object[] values,
                                          java.lang.String tableName,
                                          java.lang.String IDFieldName)
        Executes an insert statement on the database using the given columnNames, values and tableName and then executes a select statement to get the inserted record's ID. Used when we are creating a table that is then linked to other tables, as the records in the other tables cannot be created without the initial table's ID. For example when creating a record in the location table we need its ID to create records in the opening times table.
        Parameters:
        columnNames - the list of column names to insert values to in the database
        values - the list of values to insert into the database, linked to the columnNames by their index (e.g. columnNames[0] link to values[0]
        tableName - the table to insert the values to
        IDFieldName - the ID / primary key field name for the table being inserted to. Used to find the ID after insertion
        Returns:
        the ID / primary key of the record that was inserted

      • getFormattedSelect

        protected java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> getFormattedSelect(java.lang.String[] columnNames,
                                                                   java.lang.String tableName)
        Performs a select statement using the given column names and table name and then formats the output as "{ID}: {other values acquired}" (e.g. "1: Astra-Zeneca"). Used when creating drop-down selection menus, e.g. selecting which vaccine a manufacturer should produce
        Parameters:
        columnNames - the list of column names to insert values to in the database
        tableName - the table to insert the values to
        Returns:
        a list of records found by the select statement, formatted to be suitable for a drop-down selection menu

      • checkInputConditions

        protected boolean checkInputConditions(boolean displayError)
        Checks the user's input against several input criteria (specified by the input's label (the text before the input area).
        Parameters:
        displayError - if an error message should be displayed to the user, setting it to false can prevent multiple error messages being displayed if the input conditions are checked several times (e.g. if they have to be checked while the user still has more data to input)
        Returns:
        true if the input conditions meet all the criteria, false otherwise.

      • performStatements

        protected void performStatements()
        Iterates through the list of insert objects, and performs an insert SQL statement for each one. Returns to the select add page after all statements have been performed.
